               <msContents>
                  <summary>Letter from a large estate context, probably 6th century CE.  The writer mentions sending a pronoetes and symmachos to the Oxyrhynchite village of Pthochis.  He claims not to have received a response (perhaps to previous letters) and to be in need of an exemption (ἄφεμα).  Letter closes with uncertain reference to a village headman (μείζων) and a symmachos.  The only intact word in frag. B (χρεωστουμένους) indicates that the letter surely concerns a debt of some sort.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Multiple lines of text on the verso in a similarly late hand but the ink is too faded to be read clearly.</note>
                     <note type="general">Margins: A, Left and right</note>
                     <note type="general">Two fragments of a letter. Fragment B joins with Frag. A at the top left hand side of the document.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
